 hogs in the forest."]},{"name":"Lerner","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Yakov, Aron, Emanuel, Isadore, Meyer, Hyman, Moisey, Shlomo, Yaacov.","English: variant of   Larner  .","South German: habitational name for someone from Lern near Freising."]}]},{"name":"Charlotte","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["feminine diminutive of   Charles  , used in England since the 17th century. It was particulary popular in the 18th and 19th centuries, in part due to the influence of firstly  Queen Charlotte  (  1744–1818 ), wife of  George III , and secondly the novelist  Charlotte Brontë  (  1816–55 ); it has again come to prominence since the 1980s, especially in England and Australia."],"variants":[{"name":"Karlotte","meanings":["Variant of   Charlotte ."]},{"name":"Charlotta","meanings":["feminine diminutive of   Charles  , used in England since the 17th century. It was particulary popular in the 18th and 19th centuries, in part due to the influence of firstly  Queen Charlotte  (  1744–1818 ), wife of  George III , and secondly the novelist  Charlotte Brontë  (  1816–55 ); it has again come to prominence since the 1980s, especially in England and Australia."]},{"name":"Charlette","meanings":["feminine diminutive of   Charles  , used in England since the 17th century. It was particulary popular in the 18th and 19th centuries, in part due to the influence of firstly  Queen Charlotte  (  1744–1818 ), wife of  George III , and secondly the novelist  Charlotte Brontë  (  1816–55 ); it has again come to prominence since the 1980s, especially in England and Australia."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":45,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":54,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Charlotte Larner was born in 1504, in Pimlico St Peter, Middlesex, England, her father, Michael Larner, was 24 and her mother, Sarah, was 24. She married Yewin Berwidk about 1524, in Sussex, England. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 3 daughters. She died in 1563, in Sussex, England, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1504–1563":"1504–1563","1532–1602":"1532–1602","1534–Male":"1534–Surnud","1536–Female":"1536–Surnud","1538–Female":"1538–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1525–1602":"1525–1602","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1525/1532":"1525","1480":"1480","1558":"1558","1525":"1525","1536":"1536","1602":"1602","about 1538":"umbes 1538","1534":"1534","1532":"1532","about 1536":"umbes 1536","about 1534":"umbes 1534","1563":"1563","about 1524":"umbes 1524","1549":"1549","1538":"1538","1504":"1504","England":"England","Horsham, Sussex, England":"Horsham, Sussex, England","Pimlico St Peter, Middlesex, England":"Pimlico St Peter, Middlesex, England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","London, England":"London, England","Camberwell, Southwark, London, England":"Camberwell, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1504–1563":"1504–1563","1532–1602":"1532–1602","1534–Male":"1534–Kuollut","1536–Female":"1536–Kuollut","1538–Female":"1538–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1525–1602":"15